Ive been reading on the magician boards that the recent patch (a devastating one for us..most mages may end up quitting) changed how MOB aggro works.  Most are claiming that the pet is completely out taunting everyone it the group..not because of the dmg they are producing but because of their vunerability...I.E. much lower level and HP compared to other tank classes in the fight.  They have changed aggro so that the mobs instantly go for the weakest and lowest level thing on it first.  I honestly think this may be a good thing at times for us mages cause it means we can offer some legitimate dmg absorbtion to group situations (the Call of the Hero nerf however completely outweighs any benefit (which is not much...more bad than good here too) this might have), but if this is the case...this may be a very hard hitting patch on all the 60 warriors out there who worked so hard to get to 60 get the best taunting weapons and quest for the best of the best Kael armor.  <P>I don't know..I haven't played since the patch...but have any warriors noticed not being able to taunt as well off lower level players or pets anymore?  And, furthermore, do you think there will be ways around this for you all.<P>--------------------<P>Tomlyn Drayke-Lvl 55 Conjurer<BR>Fallken Stallken-Lvl 25 Rogue<BR>Prexus<P>"He knows the guy with the bandages around his ass ain't goin nowhere.  He's goin f#%king nowhere. Where you goin...nowhere!" ---"Boondock Saints"
