I noticed something as well.  Spent several hours in Highpass last night with my now 19th level warrior.  My warrior is very lightly twinked - maybe 250pp worth of gear total above what he should have.  Basically average weapons and average armor.  Also in my group was a level 15 warrior with weapons very comparable to mine (more accurately, they were SLIGHTLY better than mine), but atrocious armor (1piece of crafted, 1-2 pieces fine plate, but also ~3 pieces of ringmail, 3pieces of rawhide, 2 derv rings, etc).  It was damn near impossible to taunt off this warrior even when i was somewhat hurt and he was near full health.  I kept thinking "i MUST be imagining this".  My taunt skill was maxed (100) and my weapon skills (1hp and 1hs) were close to maxed (88-95).  Im not claiming this is new with this patch, cuz im not at all sure.  And its certainly possible that i just had an extended run of bad luck that my perception was exaggerating.  But it sure did seem like my taunt button wasnt doing a damn thing 4 times outta 5.
