<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I was grouped with mages 3 times over the last weekend.<BR>First time was in City of Mist with my cleric. We had an ogre sk as tank and she was doing a very nice job there. A mage joined the group and it went crazy. At first when the sk pulled all adds she pulled from time to time stayed on her. When a 42 mage joined and we got adds those went after the pet immediatly. <BR>If that happens with one add its not unusual and is probably caused by a mage not using assist, but if 2 or even 3 adds go after the pet it is getting strange, especially when the pet is parked behind the point where the sk turned to fight.<BR>So the pet died about every second fight. With single pulls I could see not much difference, but as i said we had a very good tank and sk's have it a bit easier with taunting than warriors with their spells.<P>Second time was sunday morning in Rathe Mountains where my druid grouped with a mage and a SK(different people than CoM).<BR>Here we didnt get adds, so it was nothing extrordinary.<BR>But mage pets died several times here too. <P>Yesterday evening, DL north wall with my cleric. Again a mage joins the group and each <BR>time the adds seem to go after the pet (main target was on puller, but even there at the beginning it seemed to face the pet).<P>From these observations over the weekend i would say that pets generate quite a bit of aggro. Not too bad (around level 40 here) that it can't be handled, but at higher levels the seconds it takes to taunt a mob off the pet might be too long.<P>I thought the first incident (CoM) as zone specific because of the pathing in there (pet <BR>was usually parked in a corner) but after all <BR>I heard from others in my guild yesterday I dont think this was some random event.<P>Gnomb Goodbasher level 48 warrior<BR>Harbromme Lifegiver level 42 cleric<BR>Ethandrea Wolfsong level 39 druid
</FONT>
